Bulk Download of World Bank Data

In this note, we introduce how to download the whole data availabe using the WDI package.

WDIbulk

Setup

library(tidyverse)
library(WDI)

If you do not have a data folder in the directry you saved this Rmd file, create it.

dir.create("data")

By the next code, we can download a list of 6 data frames: Data, Country, Series, Country-Series, Series-Time, FootNote

Download WDIbulk

wdibulk <- WDIbulk(timeout = 600)
trying URL 'https://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/WDI_csv.zip'
Content type 'application/x-zip-compressed' length 72107355 bytes (68.8 MB)
==================================================
downloaded 68.8 MB
str(wdibulk, max.level = 1)
List of 6
 $ Data          : tibble [24,902,388 × 6] (S3: tbl_df/tbl/data.frame)
 $ Country       :'data.frame': 265 obs. of  31 variables:
 $ Series        :'data.frame': 1486 obs. of  21 variables:
 $ Country-Series:'data.frame': 8241 obs. of  4 variables:
 $ Series-Time   :'data.frame': 148 obs. of  4 variables:
 $ FootNote      :'data.frame': 741689 obs. of  5 variables:

Write it in the data folder

Since it is a list, not a data frame, we need to write it using write_rds, instead of write_csv.

write_rds(wdibulk, "data/wdibulk.rds")

The data size is 3.2 GB after expanded, and the data part is 3.1 GB.

write_csv(wdibulk$Data, "data/wdi_data.csv")
write_csv(wdibulk$Country, "data/country.csv")
write_csv(wdibulk$Series, "data/series.csv")

Examples

GDP per Cap

id: NY.GDP.PCAP.PP.KD

df_gdppcap <- wdi_data |> filter(Indicator.Code == "NY.GDP.PCAP.PP.KD")
df_gdppcap <- df_gdppcap |> select(country = Country.Name, iso3c = Country.Code, year, gdppcap = value)
df_gdppcap
df_gdppcap |> distinct(country, iso3c)

A set of ids

  1. CO2 emissions (metric tons per capita) ：EN.ATM.CO2E.PC
  2. Renewable electricity output (% of total electricity output)：EG.ELC.RNEW.ZS
  3. Electricity production from oil, gas and coal sources (% of total)：EG.ELC.FOSL.ZS
  4. Electricity production from nuclear sources (% of total)：EG.ELC.NUCL.ZS
WDI_IDs <- c("EN.ATM.CO2E.PC", "EG.ELC.RNEW.ZS", "EG.ELC.FOSL.ZS", "EG.ELC.NUCL.ZS")
df_wdi_ids <- wdi_data |> filter(Indicator.Code %in% WDI_IDs)
df_wdi_ids |> distinct(Indicator.Name, Indicator.Code)
df_co2_energy <- df_wdi_ids |> select(country = Country.Name, iso3c = Country.Code, year, indicator = Indicator.Code, value) |> 
  pivot_wider(names_from = indicator, values_from = value) |>
  rename(co2pcap = `EN.ATM.CO2E.PC`, nuclear = `EG.ELC.NUCL.ZS`, fossil = `EG.ELC.FOSL.ZS`, renewable = `EG.ELC.RNEW.ZS`)
df_co2_energy

df_country_short <- df_country |> select(country = Short.Name, iso2c = WB.2.code, region = Region, income = Income.Group, lending = Lending.category)
df_country_short

Examples

GDP per Cap with Extra

df_gdppcap_extra <- df_gdppcap |> left_join(df_country_short, by = "country")
df_gdppcap_extra
df_gdppcap_ex <- df_gdppcap_extra |> select(country, iso2c, iso3c, year, gdppcap, region, income, lending) |>
  mutate(region = case_when(is.na(region) ~ "Aggreagates", 
                            TRUE ~ region), 
         income = case_when(is.na(region) ~ "Aggregates",
                            TRUE ~ region))
df_gdppcap_ex
df_gdppcap_ex |> filter(!(region == "Aggreagates")) |> distinct(country, iso2c, iso3c, region, income, lending)

Co2 vs Energy

df_co2_energy_extra <- df_co2_energy |> left_join(df_country_short, by = "country")
df_co2_energy_extra
df_co2_energy_ex <- df_co2_energy_extra |> select(country, iso2c, iso3c, year, co2pcap, nuclear, fossil, renewable, region, income, lending) |>
  mutate(region = case_when(is.na(region) ~ "Aggreagates", 
                            TRUE ~ region), 
         income = case_when(is.na(region) ~ "Aggregates",
                            TRUE ~ region))
df_co2_energy_ex
df_co2_energy_ex |> filter(!(region == "Aggreagates")) |> 
  pivot_longer(co2pcap:renewable) |> drop_na(value) |>
  ggplot(aes(year, fill = name)) + geom_bar() + 
  labs(title = "Number of Countries Having Each Data")

Example: Analysis

df_co2_energy_ex |> filter(!(region == "Aggreagates")) |> distinct(region) |> pull() |> dput()
c("South Asia", "Europe & Central Asia", "Middle East & North Africa", 
"East Asia & Pacific", "Sub-Saharan Africa", "Latin America & Caribbean", 
"North America")
regions <- c("South Asia", "Europe & Central Asia", "Middle East & North Africa", 
"East Asia & Pacific", "Sub-Saharan Africa", "Latin America & Caribbean", 
"North America")
df_co2_energy_ex |> filter(country %in% regions) |> 
  pivot_longer(co2pcap:renewable) |> drop_na(value) |>
  ggplot(aes(year, value, fill = name)) + geom_area(col = "black", linewidth = 0.1) + 
  facet_wrap(~country)
